source.name: Female mean age of childbearing (years)
source.additionalInfo:
Female mean age of childbearing (years).

The mean of an age schedule of age-specific birth rates. The age-specific birth rates may refer either to a birth cohort or a time period.

Original dataset is given in 5 year intervals:1950-1955,	1955-1960, 1960-1965, 1965-1970, 1970-1975, 1975-1980, 1980-1985, 1985-1990, 1990-1995, 1995-2000, 2000-2005, 2005-2010, 2010-2015, 2015-2020. In the uploaded dataset the first year of the interval is indicated.

United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2019).
